act = {"start": "2022-11-07 20:00", "end": "2022-11-07 22:00", "stage": "Cottage Road Cinema", "act": "Alcarr\u00e0s", "type": "film", "url": "https://www.leedsfilm.com//liff-2022-films/alcarr\u00e0s/", "blurb": "The screenings of\u00a0Alcarr\u00e0s on 8 and 10 November will include\u00a0subtitles for the D/deaf and people experiencing hearing loss.\n\"Catalan writer-director Carla Sim\u00f3n confirms the promise of her debut 'Summer 1993' in this poignant, rippling study of an extended family being forced off their farm.\" - Guy Lodge, Variety\n\"The film strikes a deft balance between idyllic reminiscence and melancholy for a cherished place...\" -\u00a0Caitlin Quinlan, Little White Lies\nWinner of the Golden Bear at the Berlinale, Alcarr\u00e0s is a beautifully observed ensemble drama full of heart. As far as they can remember, the Sol\u00e9 family have spent every summer picking the peaches from their orchard in Alcarr\u00e0s, a small village in Spain. With the sudden news that they face eviction, the Sol\u00e9s find themselves at odds as to how to go on, risking the very ties that bind them. With a remarkable cast of non-professionals, Carla Sim\u00f3n creates an authentic and moving contemplation of the fragility of family and childhood."}
