act = {"start": "2022-11-03 18:00", "end": "2022-11-03 19:28", "stage": "Vue at The Light - Screen 11", "act": "Tori and Lokita", "type": "film", "url": "https://www.leedsfilm.com//liff-2022-films/tori-and-lokita/", "blurb": "\"Masterfully crafted and unspeakably heartbreaking.\" - Leslie Felperin, Hollywood Reporter\n\"In 88 succinct and effective minutes, it sketches a heartbreaking portrait of young refugees clinging to each other in a Europe that is far from welcoming.\" - Steve Pond, The Wrap\nThe latest from the multiple Palme d\u2019Or winning Belgian duo, the Dardenne Brothers is a tender portrait of two young West African immigrants as they try to make it in the European immigration system. Inseparable friends Tori and Lokita are posing as siblings to try and secure permission for the older Lokita to stay on as a refugee. The authorities make it increasingly difficult for them to stay together as they struggle to make it. Never sentimental but heartbreakingly moving, Tori and Lokita is the finest Dardennes film for some time."}
